===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr}} ''[[#French|chamois]]'', from {{etyl|cel-gau}} {{term|camox|lang=cel-gau}} (5th c., Polemius Silvius), probably from an extinct Alpine language (Raetic, Ligurian). Compare also {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|gamiza|lang=goh}} {{gloss|"chamois"; > Modern German {{term|Gämse|lang=de}}}}.

